HEADWORD: Yumas
<hw>Yu"mas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Yuma</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A
tribe of Indians native of Arizona and the adjacent parts of Mexico and
California. They are agricultural, and cultivate corn, wheat, barley,
melons, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The a wider sense, the term sometimes includes the
Mohaves and other allied tribes.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

